<br>
2.) Board participation is required for elder council members and officers, and is HIGHLY suggested for the rest of the pack; in-game socialization is only a part of the guild experience.  Try to visit once a week if you can, while elder council members and officers should visit much more than that.<br>
<br>
3.) Cursing and Spamming guildchat is not allowed. Tho' we are more of a laid-back guild and Do have fun in guildchat we need to keep it semi-respectable. Treat your fellow guildmates with the respect you'd want to be treated with.<br>
Additionally, if you have items to sell, try not to turn guildchat into &quot;the Trade channel,&quot; instead post in the appropriate section of the web board or /join trade to have a wider sales base.  This does not apply to items for the guildbank or that are being given free to a denmate.  <br>
<br>
4.) Tho' we do like to help each other here to the mutual benefit of all that does not entitle you to expect your guildies to drop whatever They are doing to come Res/PL/chase off evils... Make your request(s) either here or in-game (depending on the situation) and if people can help they will...<br>
<br>
5.) PK policy - WoR has a PK arm, but we are not a PK guild. You do not have to go out of your way to PK. Play how you want to play. CC'ing is discouraged and LnS encouraged.  PK with honor and dignity.<br>
<br>
6.) Xteaming is not allowed. No need to assist evil or newty teams, they have their own numbers, but WoR realizes that X-teaming is a sticky subject for all, so I view &quot;X-teaming&quot; as a &quot;pre-determined&quot; plan to temporarily ally ones self with a member or members of another alliance in order to PK.  If this is the case, then it is strictly not allowed.  However, if you are under attack by one side and a member of the other side offers assistance or just joins in, the choice is yours.<br>
<br>
7.) Cursing/Spamming/Behaving like an Idiot in /ooc if frowned upon... Use your head and remember while you wear the WoR tag what you Do/Say reflects on the Entire guild... Think Before you Speak.<br>
<br>
8.) Raid/Epics Policy - While WoR has a Raid/Epic battle arm, we are not a Raid Guild in the traditional sense.  There is no requirement for you to drop everything and go on raids. <br>
<br>
9.) Same Team Training will NOT be tolerated under ANY circumstances and will be dealt with severely and quickly. If you train by accident, announce it beforehand (use hotkey), if someone on good team dies from your train, please try to make some restitution (say sorry, offer to pay for rez, etc.)<br>
<br>
10) Roleplaying Policy - Sullon Zek is a Deity Allignment PK server, but it just may be the truest form of Roleplaying we can come across.  If you wish to roleplay your character, then feel free to do so, but there is no requirement for everyone to play along.<br>
